import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['source'], data['target'])
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    plt.ylabel('Target')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between source and target?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['source'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['source'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['source'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['source'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['source'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of source?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['target'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['target'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['target'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['target'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['target'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xlabel('Target')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of target?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    source_counts = data['source'].value_counts()
    source_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the most common source value?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=source_counts.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Most common source value: {source_counts.idxmax()} ({source_counts.max():.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
